nk]]''' || align=center| WR || align=center| 1980\u20131993 || align=center style=\"border-right: 3px solid #A52A2A;\"|2008 || align=center| 89 || align=center| [[Dave Robinson (American football)|Dave Robinson]] || align=center| LB || align=center | 1973\u20131974 || align=center |2013\n|-\n| align=center| 60 || align=center| [[Dick Stanfel]] || align=center| OG || align=center| 1956\u20131958 || align=center style=\"border-right: 3px solid #A52A2A;\"|2016 || align=center|55 || align=center| [[Jason Taylor (American football)|Jason Taylor]] || align=center| DE/LB || align=center |2008 || align=center |2017\n|-\n| align=center| 24 || align=center| [[Champ Bailey]] || align=center| CB || align=center| 1999\u20132003 || align=center style=\"border-right: 3px solid #A52A2A;\"|2019 || align=center| || align=center|  || align=center|  || align=center | || align=center |\n|-\n! colspan=\"10\" style=\"text-align:center; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Washington Redskins}};\"|'''Management'''\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Name\n!Positions\n!Seasons\n!style=\"border-right: 3px solid #A52A2A;\"|Inducted\n! colspan=\"2\" |Name\n!Positions\n!Seasons\n!Inducted\n|-\n|align=center colspan=\"2\" | '''[[George Allen (coach)|George Allen]]''' || align=center| [[Coach (sport)|Head coach]] || align=center| 1971\u20131977 || align=center style=\"border-right: 3px solid #A52A2A;\"|2002 || align=center colspan=\"2\" | '''[[Ray Flaherty]]''' || align=center| Head coach || align=center| 1936\u20131942 || align=center|1976\n|-\n| align=center colspan=\"2\" | '''[[Joe Gibbs]]''' || align=center| Head coach || align=center| 1981\u20131992<br />2004\u20132007 || align=center style=\"border-right: 3px solid #A52A2A;\"|1996 || align=center colspan=\"2\" | [[Curly Lambeau]] || align=center| Head coach || align=center| 1952\u20131953 || align=center|1963\n|-\n| align=center colspan=\"2\" | [[Vince Lombardi]] || align=center| Head coach || align=center| 1969 || align=center style=\"border-right: 3px solid #A52A2A;\"|1971 || align=center colspan=\"2\" | '''[[George Preston Marshall]]''' || align=center| Owner & founder || align=center| 1932\u20131969 || align=center|1963\n|-\n|align=center colspan=\"2\" | '''[[Bobby Beathard]]''' || align=center| General Manager || align=center| 1978\u20131989 || align=center style=\"border-right: 3px solid #A52A2A;\"|2018 || align=center colspan=\"2\" |  || align=center|  || align=center|  || align=center|\n|}</center>\n\n===Washington Hall of Stars===\nThe [[Washington Hall of Stars]] is a series of banners hanging at [[Robert F. Kennedy Memorial Stadium|RFK Stadium]] honoring D.C. performers from all sports. It was previously located on a series of white-and-red signs ringing the face of the stadium's mezzanine level. Another version hangs on a large sign on one of the parking garages at [[Nationals Park]].\n\nDespite having been elected to the Pro Football Hall of Fame, Turk Edwards, Ray Flaherty, Joe Gibbs, and Paul Krause are not on the Hall of Stars banners. Edwards, Flaherty, and Gibbs had been honored on signs on the prior version of the Hall of Stars.\n\n===Redskins Ring of Fame===\nWhen the Redskins moved out of RFK Stadium, the signs commemorating the Washington Hall of Stars were left behind and the team began a new tradition of honoring Redskins greats via the \"Ring of Fame\", a set of signs on the upper level facade at FedExField. Unlike the Hall of Stars, which honors historical greats from all sports, the Ring of Fame is limited to honoring Redskins greats. The following is a list of members of the Ring of Fame:<ref>{{cite web|title=History Ring of Fame Table|url=https://www.redskins.com/news/history-ring-of-fame-table|publisher=NFL Enterprises, LLC|website=Redskins.com|access-date=August 16, 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\" width=\"auto\"\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Washington Redskins}};\"|'''Redskins Ring of Fame'''\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Washington Redskins}};\"|No.\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Washington Redskins}};\"|Name\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Washington Redskins}};\"|Position\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Washington Redskins}};\"|Tenure\n|-\n| N/A || [[George Allen (American football coach)|George Allen]] || Head coach || 1971\u20131977\n|-\n| 20 || [[Cliff Battles]] || [[Running back|RB]] || 1932\u20131937\n|-\n| 33 || [[Sammy Baugh]] || [[Quarterback|QB]] || 1937\u20131952\n|-\n| 53 || [[Jeff Bostic]] || [[Center (American football)|C]] || 1980\u20131993\n|-\n| 80 || [[Gene Brito]] || [[Defensive end|DE]] || 1951\u20131953<br />1955\u20131958\n|-\n| 43 || [[Larry Brown (running back)|Larry Brown]] || [[Running back|RB]] || 1969\u20131976\n|-\n| 65 || [[Dave Butz]] || [[Defensive tackle|DT]] || 1975\u20131988\n|-\n| 84 || [[Gary Clark]] || [[Wide receiver|WR]] || 1985\u20131992\n|-\n| 51 || [[Monte Coleman]] || [[Linebacker|LB]] || 1979\u20131994\n|-\n| N/A || [[Jack Kent Cooke]] || Owner || 1961\u20131997\n|-\n| 35 || [[Bill Dudley]] || [[Running back|RB]] || 1950\u20131951, 1953\n|-\n| N/A || [[Wayne Curry]] || [[Prince George's County, Maryland|Prince George's County]] executive || 1994\u20132002\n|-\n| 37 || [[Pat Fischer]] || [[Cornerback|CB]] || 1968\u20131977\n|-\n| 59 || [[London Fletcher]] || [[Linebacker|LB]] || 2007\u20132013\n|-\n| N/A || [[Joe Gibbs]] || Head coach || 1981\u20131992<br />2004\u20132007\n|-\n| 28 || [[Darrell Green]] || [[Cornerback|CB]] || 1983\u20132002\n|-\n| 68 || [[Russ Grimm]] || [[Guard (American football)|G]] || 1981\u20131991\n|-\n| 55 || [[Chris Hanburger]] || [[Linebacker|LB]] || 1965\u20131978\n|-\n| 57 || [[Ken Harvey (American football)|Ken Harvey]] || [[Linebacker|LB]] || 1994\u20131998\n|-\n| 56 || [[Len Hauss]] || [[Center (American football)|C]] || 1964\u20131977\n|-\n| N/A || Phil Hochberg || [[Public address|PA announcer]] || 1963\u20132000\n|-\n| 27 || [[Ken Houston]] || [[Safety (gridiron football position)|S]] || 1973\u20131980\n|-\n| 70 || [[Sam Huff]] || [[Linebacker|LB]] || 1964\u20131967, 1969\n|-\n| 66 || [[Joe Jacoby]] || [[Tackle (American football)|T]]/[[Guard (American football)|G]] || 1981\u20131993\n|-\n| 47 || [[Dick James (American football)|Dick James]] || [[Running back|RB]] || 1956\u20131963\n|-\n| 9 || [[Sonny Jurgensen]] || [[Quarterback|QB]] || 1964\u20131974\n|-\n| 22 || [[Charlie Justice (American football player)|Charlie Justice]] || [[Running back|RB]] || 1950, 1952\u20131954\n|-\n| 17 || [[Billy Kilmer]] || [[Quarterback|QB]] || 1971\u20131978\n|-\n| 14 || [[Eddie LeBaron]] || [[Quarterback|QB]] || 1952\u20131953<br />1955\u20131959\n|-\n| N/A || [[Vince Lombardi]] || Head coach || 1969\n|-\n| 72 || [[Dexter Manley]] || [[Defensive end|DE]] || 1981\u20131989\n|-\n| 71 || [[Charles Mann (American football)|Charles Mann]] || [[Defensive end|DE]] || 1983\u20131993\n|-\n| N/A || [[George Preston Marshall]] || Team founder || 1932\u20131969\n|-\n| 40 || [[Wayne Millner]] || [[End (American football)|E]] || 1936\u20131941, 1945\n|-\n| 49 || [[Bobby Mitchell]] || [[Wide receiver|WR]] || 1962\u20131968\n|-\n| 30 || [[Brian Mitchell (American football)|Brian Mitchell]] || [[Running back|RB]]/[[Return specialist|RS]] || 1990\u20131999\n|-\n| 81 || [[Art Monk]] || [[Wide receiver|WR]] || 1980\u20131993\n|-\n| 3 || [[Mark Moseley]] || [[Placekicker|PK]] || 1974\u20131986\n|-\n| 23 || [[Brig Owens]] || [[Defensive back|DB]] || 1966\u20131977\n|-\n| 16 || [[Richie Petitbon]] || [[Safety (gridiron football position)|S]]<br />Defensive coordinator/head coach || 1971\u20131972<br />1981\u20131992<br />1993\n|-\n| 65 || [[Vince Promuto]] || [[Guard (American football)|G]] || 1960\u20131970\n|-\n| 44 || [[John Riggins]] || [[Running back|RB]] || 1976\u20131979<br />1981\u20131985\n|-\n| 60 || [[Chris Samuels]] || [[Offensive tackle|T]] || 2000\u20132009\n|-\n| 87 || [[Jerry Smith (American football)|Jerry Smith]] || [[Tight end|TE]] || 1965\u20131977\n|-\n| 42 || [[Charley Taylor]] || [[Wide receiver|WR]] || 1964\u20131977\n|-\n| 21 || [[Sean Taylor]] || [[Safety (gridiron football position)|S]] || 2004\u20132007\n|-\n| 7 || [[Joe Theismann]] || [[Quarterback|QB]] || 1974\u20131985\n|-\n| N/A || Lamar \"Bubba\" Tyer || Athletic trainer || 1971\u20132002<br />2004\u20132008\n|-\n| 17 || [[Doug Williams (American football)|Doug Williams]] || [[Quarterback|QB]] || 1986\u20131989\n|}\n\n===The 80 Greatest Redskins===\n[[File:May, Mark (USAF).jpg|thumb|upright|right|[[Mark May]], [[offensive lineman]] for the Redskins between [[1981 Washington Redskins season|1981]] and [[1989 Washington Redskins season|1989]], was named one of the [[70 Greatest Redskins]]]]\nIn honor of the Redskins' 70th anniversary, on June 13, 2002, a panel selected the 70 Greatest Redskins to honor the players and coaches who were significant on-field contributors to the Redskins five championships and rich history. They were honored in a weekend of festivities, including a special halftime ceremony during the Redskins' 26\u201321 win over the [[Indianapolis Colts]].<ref name=greatest>{{cite web|title=80 Greatest Redskins|url=https://www.redskins.com/team/history/80-greatest-redskins|publisher=NFL Enterprises, LLC|website=Redskins.com|access-date=April 6, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Kring-Schreifels|first=Jake|title=Rewarding Moments In Redskins History: 70 Greatest Honored|url=https://www.redskins.com/news/rewarding-moments-in-redskins-history-70-greatest-honored|publisher=NFL Enterprises, LLC|website=Redskins.com|date=November 15, 2018|access-date=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe panel that chose the 70 consisted of former news anchor [[Bernard Shaw (journalist)|Bernard Shaw]]; former player [[Bobby Mitchell]]; Senator [[George Allen (U.S. politician)|George Allen]] (son of coach [[George Allen (coach)|George Allen]]); broadcaster [[Ken Beatrice]]; Noel Epstein, editor for the [[The Washington Post|Washington Post]]; former diplomat [[Joseph J. Sisco]]; Phil Hochberg, who retired in 2001 after 38 years as team stadium announcer; Pro Football Hall of Fame historian Joe Horrigan; sportscaster [[George Michael (sportscaster)|George Michael]]; sports director [[Andy Pollin]]; NFL Films president [[Steven Sabol]]; and news anchor [[Jim Vance]].<ref name=greatest />\n\nThe list includes three head coaches and 67 players, of which 41 were offensive players, 23 defensive players and three special teams players.<ref name=greatest />\n\nAmong the 70 Greatest, there are 92 [[Super Bowl]] appearances, with 47 going once and 45 playing in more than one. 29 members possess one Super Bowl ring and 26 have more than one. Also, before the Super Bowl, members of the 70 made 18 World Championship appearances including six that participated in the Redskins' NFL Championship victories in 1937 and 1942.<ref name=greatest />\n\nOn August 24, 2012, ten more players and personnel were added to the list for the team's 80th anniversary.<ref>{{cite news|last=Tinsman|first=Brian|title=Ten Newest Greatest Redskins Announced|url=https://www.redskins.com/news/ten-newest-greatest-redskins-announced-8049634|publisher=NFL Enterprises, LLC|website=Redskins.com|date=August 24, 2012|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{col-begin|width=auto}}\n{{col-break}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Washington Redskins|border=2}};\"|#\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Washington Redskins|border=2}};\"|Name\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Washington Redskins|border=2}};\"|Position\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Washington Redskins|border=2}};\"|Years\n|-\n|21\n|[[Terry Allen (American football)|Terry Allen]]\n|RB\n|1995\u201398\n|-\n|56\n|[[LaVar Arrington]]\n|LB\n|2000\u201305\n|-\n|41\n|[[Mike Bass]]\n|CB\n|1969\u201375\n|-\n|20\n|[[Cliff Battles]]\n|B\n|1932\u201337\n|-\n|33\n|[[Sammy Baugh]]\n|QB\n|1937\u201352\n|-\n|31\n|[[Don Bosseler]]\n|FB\n|1957\u201364\n|-\n|53\n|[[Jeff Bostic]]\n|C\n|1980\u201393\n|-\n|4\n|[[Mike Bragg]]\n|P\n|1968\u201379\n|-\n|